# Non-Standard LaTeX Code

In posts,

* `@@` is used to delimit in-line LaTeX code, and `%%` is used to delimit block
  formulas. This is defined in `_layouts/base.html`.
* the user-defined `\nl` command is usually used instead of `\\` for line
  breaks, so as to not mess up the Markdown parser
* a backslash is placed before the `*` in commands like `\begin{align*}`

Do not use this formatting in your responses. Use standard LaTeX formatting for
those. This information is only to help you read my posts.

## Example

If @@n@@ is a positive integer, then

%%
\begin{align\*}
\sum_{i=1}^n i
&= \frac{n \cdot (n+1)}{2} \nl
&= \frac{1}{2} n^2 + \frac{1}{2} n.
\end{align\*}
%%
